	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(center)"><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The Fruit of the Righteous is a Tree of Live&#44; and the Lips of Truth shall be Remembered Forever.</p>
				<p><hi rend="bold">A Memorial Offering</hi><lb/> Upon the death of that great&#44;<lb/> wise&#44; good&#44; and beloved<lb/> man&#44;<lb/> MINISTER AND GUIDE<lb/> OF THE<lb/> Congregation &#8220;Beth&#45;el&#45;Emeth&#44;&#8221;<lb/> <placeName>PHILADELPHIA</placeName>.</p>
				<p>ALAS&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName><hi rend="bold">I</hi>saac Leeser</persName> is gathered.  Woe&#33; He&#39;s departed and is no more&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">S</hi>adness and mourning on <placeName>Israel</placeName> fall&#44; for the affliction is sore.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">A</hi>h&#33; thus on the Holy <date>Sabbath</date> his spirit ascended on high.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">A</hi>nd faint grew our hearts&#44; and midst weeping and wailing&#44; a cry</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">C</hi>ame from Heaven and called him&#44; and broke up our circle of joy.</p>
				<p></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">L</hi>o&#33; where is the scribe&#44; who his wisdom can fitly applaud&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">E</hi>ternal his teachings&#44; in all tongues they are scattered abroad.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">E</hi>ver abounding in reverence&#44; in wisdom&#44; and piety&#39;s praise&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">S</hi>till on Holy ground walking he left us exalted in grace&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">E</hi>ver in him was our shield&#44; as still on his strength we relied&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName><hi rend="bold">R</hi>everend Isaac Leeser</persName> enough for our glory&#59; our guide.</p>
				<p></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">Blest</hi> are the righteous.  Though dead they still live for the truth&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">Be</hi> like him&#44; whose loins were girded with strength in his youth.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">The</hi> grave we can&#39;t know&#44; nor see destruction&#39;s abyss&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">Righteous</hi> I pray&#44; in God&#39;s will&#44; may my end be like his.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">ISAAC GOLDSTEIN</persName>&#44; <placeName>137 HUDSON STREET&#44; N. Y.</placeName></p>
				<p rend="Note&#58; ">Same <add>&#63;</add> text in Hebrew on the right side of the page&#59; picture of <persName>Isaac Leeser</persName> near the top center of the page</p>
